12-03-2026
implementing polyglot openings book
compatibility:
square indexing a1 = 0 h8 = 63  (opposite from mine)
move encoding: 0000 000000 000000
                 ||  start  dest
                 \/
        3 bits promotion piece

promotion values: 
0       none
1 << 12 knight 
2 << 12 bishop
3 << 12 rook
4 << 12 queen

castling is just a king move that moves 2 squares
enpassant is encoded like a normal capture but you have the enpassant square of the position (state)
enpassant square is only included in the hash if there is an actual enpassant capture otherwise its neglected

zobrist hashing: exact same hash algorithm and constants 781 constants (12 * 64 + 4 + 8 + 1)

piece indicies are reversed: 0-5 white p n b r q k 6-11 black

castline rights indexing: 
0 white king side
1 white qs
2 black ks
3 black qs

book file format: 16 bytes sorted by key
uint64_t key
uint16 move
uint16 weight
uint32 learn

algorithm for openings book:
1. compute polyglot hash
2. binary search file for hash
3. collect all entries with the key
4. choose move (usually weighted random)

-> this is a lot of pretty deep architectural stuff so i might just make some kind
of plugin to compute the polyglot hash and just adjust the move to uint16 cause
this makes sense from a performance perspective but changing eg the square indexing 
doesnt have any effect on performance

bitboards_utils and legal_move_utils merged into single file util

implemented full perft suite with multiple positions at depth 5
MOVE -> 16bit Successfull
tested with full perft suite

polyglot hashing implemented todo fix to match examples in original doc

